\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could you give me your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Ruth Robinson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 193 Main Street, Newthorpe, Notts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your marital status, you're a widow aren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 15th - 10th of July 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 18th of December 1891.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your birth place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Millthorpe in the parish of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10957874  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Greazley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I was eighteen when we left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you lived there eighteen years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 At the - Chestnut Farm, Moorgreen, Newthorpe, Notts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So that was round about 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 '10.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you move again from 1910 onwards up to about 1918 can you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When he - when I - oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were born in 1891?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I was 
- when my youngest brother was born mother was forty-two. The same December. So he was a year - I was a year and a month older than him, so I should be born - how old would mother be - forty - forty. She was born in 1840 - 1849 mother. Yes. My youngest br
other was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So that makes your father how old when you were born then, forty-one or forty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, she was forty-two when my brother - youngest brother was born so she'd be forty. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Father - mother'd be forty-wouldn't she.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So that would make your father what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Forty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A place called Campton in Bedfordshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Farm labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he have another job before or after he was a farm labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 After.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of job was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He left farming and went to live in London and helped to dig for St Pancras Station. Yes. Helped to dig the turf to - for the station.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Apart from his job as a farm labourer did he have any casual or part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 'Til he went - 'til he went on the - St Pancras Station. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did he do after that, after St Pancras?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He left St - he had to leave St Pancras station, get out of town to get back on the land. And he came out of Bedfordshire right i
nto - Greazley parish, Nottinghamshire. No - we moved in 1915 to number 11 Baldwin Street, Newthorpe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was the year you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Same year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15492673\charrsid10957874 many}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I had - there was - seven sisters - seven daughters and eight brothers - eight - that was fifteen in all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There were fifteen of you altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember the order in which they were born and how they were spaced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can't remember the date of - the first one. 
Well do you want me to give you the - just these. Yes. Annie Gaunt, born June 7th 1873. Arthur }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Charles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 Gaunt, January 6th 1875. George Henry Gaunt, April 9th 1876. Mary Eliza }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Gaunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , November 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  1877. Jane Gaunt, January 16th 1880. Ernest Gaunt, September
 11th 1881. 1881. John Gray Gaunt, August 9th 1883. William Gaunt, October - William Gaunt, October 2nd 1885. Samuel James Gaunt, January 31st 1887. Sara Louisa Gaunt, April 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 nd}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  1890. Ruth Gaunt, December 18th 1891. Charles Albert Gaunt, January 17th 1893. That's - and then of course the other three died as babies - three died as - babies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Are they included in that list?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, they're not in here. That makes the fifteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What years were they born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well mother lost her first two
 you see. And mother - have you got it off - let's see, mother was born in 1849 and she was married a year when her first baby was born. Father was - mother was a year older than father and he was twenty-one - he - mother was twenty-one and father twenty.
 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was quite a big family wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15492673\charrsid10957874  it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 was in those days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15492673\charrsid10957874 Will}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  you take it off a minute. John Gaunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How old was your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - when he died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Up to here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And worked at the Caswell farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 As a farm labourer again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he do that 'til he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. He worked at - there was a - about nine years a farm labourer. And then he - started leading coal for the colliery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - you see the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 colliers\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  coals. They're taking a load out - for the - he worked for the - the Bobby Walkers. And - and - as a carter, yes. Yes, leading the coals. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How long did he do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well he - I couldn't just say how long and then he worked for Digby Colliery
 Company and he was leading coals there. And then of course he - dad had got the do-key down there. He started with a donkey and my brothers and sisters used to go round with hayless barn from the brewery. And then he went from a donkey to a horse and he 
gradually worked his way up - he worked for Baysford Rural District Council - on the road, making the roads, using stone and etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was this a sort of a contractor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 On his own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was self employed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. He finished with collie
ry leading, leading the coals and then he worked for himself until he was a farmer. And he - he rented a lot of land before we went to the farm and then he went as a farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was a farmer in his own right then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, yes. In 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was up 'til he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. No, then he - 'cos he retired in 1915. And came to live here. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And he lived here until he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, I don't think he was ever out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your mother was a year older than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, well - she was forty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A place called Mepashall. Mepashall, in Bedfordshire. Yes. Next village to Campton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She used to make straw hats with this - from - they came from Luton, the straw. She was a straw hatter, used to work making hats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In her own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, in their own - they all did it in their own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 do any work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
She went into service - oh, she went into service before she was married. And then of course she was married when she was twenty-one, so - there was no time for anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So she had no part time jobs then either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No way whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many rooms were there in the house where you were born can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we call it a six roomed house. Three bedrooms and three downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What would you call reception rooms, there were two of them I suppose?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There's the living room and a parlour. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did anyone else besides your parents and brother and sisters live in the house? Other relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we had a young man come to live with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 As a lodger was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, but he wasn't with us long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just for a short time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, because my - there was always one daughter kept at h
ome and my brothers used to help quite a lot. One daughter left to service, another one grew up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. All done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother used to 
make our - just a few of ours, cut 'em down from other clothes you see. No, she wasn't a dressmaker but she used to - make some of our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were they new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh secondhand. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where were they bought from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we had good friends and we had aunts that was rather well-to-do and we got them from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But your new clothes?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\tx7560\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7233194 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - new clothes, we had 'em - some from the stores and some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 Willis Crofts at Ilkeston, the tailors.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7233194 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
What do you call the stores?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The Co-operative - the Co-op. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother traded with a man named William Alcock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was he like a small cobbler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was a - there was cobblers and a big shop in Eastwood. Yes. He sold shoes and he were - his son was a cobbler too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father help your mother with the cleaning and cooking and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well he used to help with the cooking quite a lot. Yes. And he always helped to serve the meals out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And decorating and repairs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother used to do - the decorating, except the living room and we generally had a man to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father do any sort of work in the house that you might call improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he take any part in the dressing and undressing and bathing of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, when we was all little. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he used to read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother used to read quite a lot, father wasn't very good at reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you went out with your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he ever have to look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Tasks that you used to do about the home to help you mother and father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - I used to help to wash 
up and then - see we had a milk round in those days when I was a girl. You see, father kept cows and we rented land and I used to take milk out night and morning. That was before we went to the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you do any of these jobs after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I never left home. I stayed at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Now about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was one brother younger than me and he went to work at the colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was when you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. I never left home 'til I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about the other children, I suppose the older ones would be looking after the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - well they did while they - 'til they got married off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And some of them went into service didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was four sisters followed each other into service and one brother, he was a groom for five year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 This would be pretty well just after leaving school would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. When I was - of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Quite a few of them went into domestic service of one kind or another didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Four sisters. I - but I had to stay at home to help mother. I was the last one at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the younger children ever help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The - the old - the older ones - the older ones helped the younger ones. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  much the younger ones could do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, well you see - as they grew up they helped one another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 It was like a general - everybody helped out where they could?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And after my sister got married they used to come home and help mother quite a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. We had to go to bed between eight and nine. Yes. 'Til we was quite grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What do you mean by grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - we had to be in for nine when I was twenty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother always put us to bed, yes, when we was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 About what age were you then when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - about eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 My sister and I shared it. And the bed - the boys had a bedroom to themselves, two big beds in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So the sleeping arrangements for the family, you had three bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The girls were in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The boys in another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had to go through the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 boys\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  room to our room but we had a room to ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your mother and father had the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But of course you always had some going away didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, they were going away and - you see, they'd - they used to come home for holidays but - there was - as one grew up they went away and then they got married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we had to bath in - at late at night at fr
ont of the fire. Yes. When we grew bigger we was always left - the girls left and the boys left to themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often did you used to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh ever Saturday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have clean clothes to put on when you had a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 normally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  the change of clothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. And then when we went to live at the farm we had a separate wash house. And a big copper in that. And we had a tremendous big bath, and of course we could all just go in and lock ourselves in and bath there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you have the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If we had company we used to use the parlour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 On the open stove. In the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What they call an open range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. No gas stove. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 About eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What members of the family would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - I can remember nine of us being at home all 
together. Then it - as they got married it gradually go to there were only - only myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So all those that were in the house would be having breakfast together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And mother and father eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That would be all at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. We had a very big table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 For breakfast? Oh - tea. Eggs and bacon and bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have anything different on certain special days such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we generally ate - unless we had boiled ham, we always had eggs and bacon, keeping fowls you see and - pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you have at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had an ordinary dinner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 About five o'clock we had tea. And if we wanted any supper we just had what we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Mother always baked her own bread. We used to have a ten stone bag of flour at the bottom of the stairs, it used to stand there on a big box. And we - was that - we had it from the miller that we got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 corn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 for the horse and that. She always baked her own bread, about three times a week. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 
We never had no baker's bread.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She made all her own jam, see, we had a big garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, she didn't do any bottling in her time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - always did the pickles, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about wine - homemade wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Father used to make a lot of homemade wine. Yes. All kinds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, the medicines that we used to have was brimstone and treacle you know, flower of sulphur.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was any beer brewed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Just wine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We grew all our own vegetables but not much fruit, only - currants, red currants and white - white currants and black currants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But not the bit stuff like pears or apples?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No. We had - we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 apple}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  trees here but we had none in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you used to buy fruit did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But you wouldn't have to buy many vegetables would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh no, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were tinned or dried vegetables or fruit about in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - tinned fruit was, used to have an odd tin of fruit but we was having plenty of fresh fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was any livestock kept for the family, hens or pigs or goats, you mentioned a couple of cows didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, we had cows and then my brother used to keep rabbits, have I put that down, did I? My brother Sam used to keep rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who looked after the livestock then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Father. Yes. And my brothers. And of course I learnt to milk when I was nine - we had cows when we lived down here you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were quite happy and active in this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Milking them and taking it round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. I enjoyed - I - I - it was my ambition go to Canada really, but I didn't like leaving mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had it - nearly every day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we'd no tinned meat in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever get extra such as rabbits from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had rabbits and poultry and all that kind, 'cos we kept them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about poaching, did you ever get involved in any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No, we had - when we lived on the farm father could - shoot rabbits or catch rabbits but he couldn't shoot any game. No. Allowed to - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often would he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In the harvest time. Yes. More so than any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having to have less food than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, we always had plenty of good food, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He didn't have to have any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Not allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, sometimes it was Hobson's choice, that or nothing. But we - generally had what mother cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  attitude if you left some food that you couldn't eat on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they'd say we should have less next time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We was never overfed, we had just enough in a way of speaking so there was really no waste.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ask for someone to pass things like the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes, we were allowed to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. If there was any left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had to be very good at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When we'd all finished. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, we had our own place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How was the meal served and who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well in those days we generally had the pudding first. Mother served it. Father used to carve the meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What order were you served in? Did you have any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we just passed round to us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did the very young ones sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well mother had two high chairs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother was a very nice person. Every - everyone admired her really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh, he was very - rather hard and a bit strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we had to do as we was told and - behave in a right way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents bring you up to behaves towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We were a very happy family 'til after we was all married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - father never allowed us - the brothers to - chastise their sisters at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He kept them in strict control?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. He - he could do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They used to hope we should grow up straight and all - father did taught us all to be honest. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Father - he did not go to chur
ch himself but he did - insist that we went to Sunday school. And he wanted - we all - all went, same as my brothers used to go to the church and then in the - in the - the last three others went to the Baptist chapel, the one that stands at the top of Pi
tfall, I went there when I was about three, and I've gone ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh we was never allowed to use - I never remember my mother swearing in her life. Father did when he - of course if he'd had extra beer or if he'd been annoyed at the market when he used to go to market. But not much indoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He wouldn't do it anyway in front of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he wouldn't allow us to swear too. No, we never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Unless we was asked anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were sent to bed. We was never - never thrashed. That was our worst - going to bed. The moment we'd had our tea we'd hav
e to go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Which one sent you, either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Either mother or father, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was a sort of real punishment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Punishment. Yes, yes, it was in those days when you heard others playing out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often do you think that this used to happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh not very often. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And either parent would punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, mother would send us, yes, just the same, if we done anything wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember any particular thing that made them punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I remember - we was coming home from school one day and we run some young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 calves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and my youngest brother got hold of one of the calves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  tails and we had to go to bed for a week for that. Every night as soon as we'd had tea. After we'd done our - what we had to do. That - that was the worst punishment I think we ever had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember how you felt about the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we knew we'd done wrong and we just had to put up with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would you say that you recieved the ideas you had about how to beha
ve from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, me father said a thing we knew - we knew he meant it and mother didn't interfere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I suppose she would back him up in most things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - you see - they didn't punish us much, she did do. She backed him up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you get the impression that she might not support him if she thought he was too strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If he hadn't have been too strict she would have let - she would have been more lenient with us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Sort of balance it up a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we could have friends for a party. Yes. Just a few friends, yes. Yes. When we went to school that was. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we had nice presents. Especially with my elder brother and sisters being married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - oh we used to look forward
 - when we was children we looked forward to the stocking in those days. Which used to be orange and apples and nuts and perhaps a new penny or sixpence. If you got sixpence we thought we'd got a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Any activity you did together with your mother or father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No, we just had Christmas Day, we used to have a big chicken or - turkey and have the ordinary Christmas. Of course we was pleased with what - and in those days we used to go out - what they call Christmas Boxing. We used to 
go to all the pubs, start at the Black Bull here, when we were children, start at the Black Bull that used to be - it's closed now - top of the street here. Yes. Just at the top of - only about two - next door to the butchers. And it's a private house now
, that was the Black Bull. They used to give us a - used to have a string bag. They used to give us a orange and we used to get another orange from the Forresters and father didn't - never went in the Forresters much. Went to that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was another pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes, but they used to give all the children the same, and then we used to come to the butchers and he lived here then but we used to get the orange from the butchers shop, we used to have about two dozen oranges by the time we'd finished, right th
rough the village. And that was - an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 d then we used to go to Barbers at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Land Close. In - no in Moorgreen. Between Moorgreen and Underwood. Then the reservoir. And we used to go there and we sometimes got a threepenny bit there. And we'd have this bag - stri
ng bag with oranges and then go and slide on the reservoir, 'cos in those days we had Christmas it was more ice and snow - different - the seasons were different. You see, I think the water - the war altered all the seasons. And - we used to go and play t
here perhaps 'til - getting on for dinner time. Then we used to go home and have Christmas dinner. And all these oranges.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 This was called Christmas Boxing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, that was Christmas Boxing. Yes. It was wonderful time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No we didn't. They couldn't afford to buy anything. I used to - long for a piano. My father did say he would buy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874  me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  a - a violin, or fiddle he called it and I said, oh I wouldn't play it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there anyone in the family who could sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Two of my sisters could sing pretty well but not - they didn't go professional or anything, just for the chapel or at concerts or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have a sort of musical evening at home with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Father used to like to play cards with us. And dominoes. And I learnt to play draughts when I was five, an old gentleman learnt me and - of course I was a good draught player. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, plenty of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. Used to have a comic - a comic paper when we was little. And then mother used to have the Christian Herald. The Christian Herald, in those days, that was a rather religious - a good paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Weekly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Weekly. And then we had the Evening News - Nottingham Evening News. The Advertiser, used to be a ha'penny in those days and - then we had a morning paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You remember your father and mother reading then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother was a very good reader, but father had to spell his way, he wasn't so good scholar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother did. Mother used to read to father too. In - especially in the latter days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember funerals in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Well my sister Annie, that was a big blow to mother. She died when she was - twenty-eight. Twenty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who would attend that sort of funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we all attended, I never forget it, I was about 
eleven, my brother was nine and - that was the one, that was her and her husband. And she - that was a big blow to mother and she buried at the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Eastwood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  Cemetery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you all went to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We all went to the funeral, yes. But the tr
ouble was, when she died at the Friday night, that's my brother, his wife died on the Saturday morning. And they was both brought home - my sister Annie was brought to - down Stanford Street, New Thorpe, from Nottingham - from Doctor Meakie's private nurs
i
ng home. And my brother's wife, Vina, was brought to her mother's who lived on the canal side. And they was in - I don't know if you know Newthorpe Common much do you. You know where it is, well there's what they call Halls Lane. Well right down Halls Lan
e
 their mother lived on the canal side. And she was brought from Bolsover, his wife, yes, that's my brother and his - that's my oldest sister and my - that's the - he comes next to - that's George Henry Gaunt, we called him Harry, and that's Jane Gaunt and
 that's Annie Gaunt. No, that's Mary - Mary Eliza. She married a Sergeant in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Metropolitan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 Police. Yes, we all attended that funeral - there was a very big blow to mother. 'Cos she was a lot older than me. And then a year after he went to Canada. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 At the funeral did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 wear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, we had crepe on our hats and - crepe black, and then we had - we had a new dress and it was - had to be grey. That's how they wore the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 mourning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  in those days. And that was only when we was girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you taken out visiting neighbours and friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had a pony and trap and father used to take us out quite a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, we used to go to market you see, I used to go to market with father. Eve
ry Saturday he used to go to Nottingham cattle market. And I used to go round the shops and meet him at the cattle market to bring the things home in the pony and trap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever go out with just your father, on these occasions you did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh that was just father, yes, and then sometimes mother would accompany him and go into the - into Nottingham if we wanted any - clothes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about other outings with your parents - Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We used to go - no, we never went much on - we used
 to go to Ilkeston flower show on a Bank Holiday Monday with mother and father, when we was little children. And then of course we used to - I had a bicycle and used to go out on us won when I was about - fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. We went to relatives. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 For a week. In the school holidays. Summer, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Which members of the family went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The younger ones. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Whereabouts usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we used to go up to London quite a lot because you see my - both my sisters they lived in London. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of things did you used to do on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well, walking all over London really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Looking at the sights in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Going to the zoo and - going to shows and plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 On the weekends when you were a child can you tell me how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - used to have a ride round on the bike and then when the - when - where }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Woolworth\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  is today, the Empire, when that was opened of course we used to go there on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we had to go to chapel on Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have different clothes on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Always have a second -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, wasn't allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents think it wrong then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We could read books, have books out but no games. Not on a Sunday. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mother always did but father didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What denomination was your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Church of England really, but she finished up - she couldn't get to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 
Greazley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  church, it was a matter of walking in those days, unless father took her in the trap. He had a pony when he retired.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 
 But}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  she got that she couldn't go to church and so she finished up at the Baptist chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often would she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Every Sunday night. Evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. We used to have afternoon service in those days, sometimes she'd get, if she felt like it, but when she got older s
he used to go to evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you attend the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, yes, we always had to attend. Sometimes in the afternoon service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - they had a - we went to Sunday school until we were bigger and older 
and then we went in the choir and - attended evening - afternoon and evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about Sunday school outings, did you have any of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we used to go on an outing - once a year to Skegness or Mablethorpe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And that was organised by the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 By the Sunday school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What other social activities were organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had a - what they call a Band of Hope. And then we had prizes if we could write about anything out of the Bible. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes, I was in the choir 'til I was married, my daughter's in now. She's married, she'll soon be fifty-five and she's been ever - ever since she was a child she's gone there and she comes from Nutall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you've got a long connection with this chapel then in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What other activities did you involve in at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had all sorts of concerts. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the chapel run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, there's nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Any other activities that you can think of that the chapel used to organise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well we used to have the concerts and - and then you used to have social evenings. Yes. So the school children could all get together, and when the bigger - when 
we were big we went to social evenings. After I was married we had quite a lot, my husband used to go. There were nothing else. Nothing else. No, unless you went to Nottingham and - to the Empire at Nottingham or see a play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So the local chapel supplied religious activities and entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Every - all the amusements. Yes. Yes. We had some wonderful concerts there. Then when I was married I always longed for a piano and that were the first thing my husband brought, and I've got it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874  today}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . But I 
couldn't - I'd gone past learning. I did have a month - but I thought it was no good but I wouldn't mine - they want me to part, not while I'm alive, you can do what you like when I'm gone. And my daughter - had lessons, she learnt when she was nine. 'Til
 
she was thirteen, and she didn't - she went in for exams but she wasn't ever so strong so we didn't - let her go on. She had the - she had the exams and then she left off when she was thirteen years old. My son had a violin. And he learnt - he went to lea
r
n when he were about eight, and he was a marvellous violinist. He passed all before him and his father used to sit and take - keep time for him and he was under a very good Italian - music teacher. Her name was Miss Anita Waite of Peel Street, Nottingham.
 
And a friend, but not far, she lives at Kimberley today - a Miss Allen used to play the piano for him for exam pieces. And he got all his letters in the July that his father died in August. In 1934. He'd got his letters, he'd got all his - he was going in
 
- he was going in for the cap and gown. This teacher said - but - when his father died - a month after he was buried he opened his violin and he banged it down and he's never played it since. And up to then, when his father were alive, he used to play at 
t
he anniversary, they had - used to have an orchestral for the anniversary, and then he used to play at all the concerts, he's gone to ever so many chapels to play. And he's got two violins in the - lobby upstairs but he - he - that broke his heart, when h
e banged it down because his - and I think that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 he really got the shock of his father's death. Yes. And he - 'course he never played it since, he shouldn't play now, and yet he loves to hear music. He could play the piano with Anne lovely. Just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 by}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  ear that is. But he - the violin he know that - when they come on the telly he's very interested, but he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 play his violin, no. He suffers a lot of shell shock you know, and that's brought it all back. You see, he had seven operations while he was at war. 
And they took him in A1 and sent him out C5. That's where I got the pension, it took me two year to get a pension. Oh he was ruined through the war. He was as bright lad as ever you saw but - there's something even today - but if you met on the road when 
he's gone by your place, sometimes he'll shout out. And - I used to put Bamber Gascoigne }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
n, well do you know, he's dead against him. I daren't have it on now. He just - he just goes in for that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Well - only when we was little at mother's knee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well in those days it was Liberal and Tory wasn't it and I think one time father was a Tory th
en he changed to Liberal. Yes. He never talked much about politics. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you've got no sort of idea why he held the views he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How about your mother, did she have any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, she'd no interest whatever. With having a large family she'd plenty to do. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember your father or mother ever voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They always voted. Always went to vote. It was - it was secret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You don't know which party they voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In some places at that time men felt they were risking their jobs or their house if they voted differently from their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you know if your father ever felt himself under any pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, none whatever, he wouldn't have anything to - no one would - persuade him any way, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was he a member of a political party at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Or working for one of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they take part in any activity in the political field other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time, what sort of activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see, when we was on the farm we always at work
, there was nothing - yes. And then when he retired of course he - he had a pony and trap and he used to go out sometimes in that that were all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, only just going to chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did she ever go out to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh she went out with friends. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Friends from the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When did your father get home from work in the evenings? About what time would he finish work, I suppose it would depend on the seasons?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see, just depends what - the harvest - whether it was harvest time or whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well it just depend. After he retired he never went out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh he used to go to a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A local pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In this younger days, not so much in his older days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Mother was very - she would not go inside a pub. That was one of mother's no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he used to go to the shows or anything of that but he didn't go in them for any sport. There wasn't much in those days you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he go to the races for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 No,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and he didn't do any gambling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He didn't bet at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your father or your mother belong to any savings clubs, sick fund or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was a member of the Oddfellowes - in - from Bedfordshire and he kept in that Lodge
 - well we were all happy together. There was no quarrelling amongst us at all while we was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I'm very close to my - all my sisters and to this boy's father and another brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 As a child who did you play with, your brothers and your sisters or other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, and then people in the yard. All the children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we had to play in the street in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we used to have battledore and shuttlecock, play marbles. And - battledore and shuttlecock. Yes. That was a girls - game.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well if we did we had to go straight and wash when we get in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Well}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  - of course we - was allowed really but we - used to get reprimanded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased, could you play with any children in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - in those days you sort of had to keep away from some. If they was rough and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The ones you would call them rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well there was some rough and some was a bit rude and - of course - we was kept away from them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you belong to any youth organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, only at the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. There was none in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any hobbies while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I were always very fond of a cat and a dog. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you collect anything like stamps for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Or gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we - I did a lot of gardening and - and - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Or walks or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we used to - used to ride my bicycle. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who did you go with normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 With friends. I have a friend now what lives at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Moorend}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , I've had a long letter from her this Christmas, we had many a ride, biking, and she's seventy-eight. And she was bred and born here. And lives at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you've known each other all over the years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, only just what we had at the chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I used to go to theatre at Nottingham when I was grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But as a child can you remember going to any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Only to concerts. At the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well, you see, there wasn't many cinemas, we used to go to a - what they used to call a 
Teddy Rainer's show and she used to only pay tuppence, that was a open - that was a tent and just local acting you know with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Teddy Rainer's. Yes. Yes. That were the man - the - as owned it and it was all his family what
 did the acting. Yes. Was - such as Maria Martin in Death in the Red Barn and all those sort - they used to play those. In this big - and that was held in the Sun Inn Croft at Eastwood. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, at the back, at the back here, that's wh
ere their tent was. Just an open - big tent - like a marquee. Pay tuppence to go there. And they - it was so rough they used to call it blood and thunder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we always had a little bit of pocket money, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well if I got two shillings I was well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was it regular, did you get a regular sum every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, and if we went out anywhere we was always given us some to go with. May into Nottingham to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 theatre or anything, when we grew up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of things did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh we'd go and book at the theatre or the Empire and - then come home, then pay the train fare, there were no - no trams, no buses, nothing in those days. Only railway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you'd spend your pocket money on little outings would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, because you see, what my sisters couldn't do my brothers used to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So it was all done within the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Within the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I don't ever remember her being very ill long, she might have been in bed three days, I remember once when
 she had a bad ache about, but that's - she wasn't one that was ill very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about when she was having the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You see. I was the next to the youngest, I can't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you don't know how she got on during her confinement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I - I think people helped her, she - I don't know who used to help but as my sisters grew up they used to be there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any relatives living nearby, did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The nearest one was one aunt at Nottingham, mother's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see - I was only very young when she died and - they saw her two or three times a year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would that be at her place or your place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She'd come to see mother. Then mother would take us to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh mother had a lot of friends, she met at the chapel and they used to come and see her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She'd see them mostly at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And they'd come to our house, quite a few friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So she'd part of a little sort of circle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well, he made friends out but it was more in the pub, he used to go in the pub he did. That's where he met his friends. Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he used to bring them home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No, they never came home. No, he'd just meet them there or at the market. Sometimes he would never go out from weekend to the other. Just depends how he felt and - there was always plenty to do you see and he were tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did any of these friends call in the house casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, a lot come and have a drink of wine with him. Yes, homemade wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They didn't have to wait to be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh no, they'd call in casually, just to see how we was or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh we had good neighbours in the yard, very good neighbours. Yes. Mother was one that helped people a lot. Sat up with them and - when they was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh they'd go in the pony and trap. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We're often told that in those days you had to make your own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I think it was just a matter of talking about the farms and things more than anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Don't think so. I don't remember any of them. Not even the elderly people in those days was not - musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Many people divide society into different social classes don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we used to think there was better off and money you see. And - that was the only way I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who would you regard as those with money and better off sort of group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well there wasn't many the working class people round about here with money, it was only like the Barbers and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you had the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Then the others were employers and people of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Which sort of group would your family fall into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well just the working class I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Other people who belonged to your group, what sort of jobs did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they had all sorts you see - father had a friend, he was the wheelwright.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was he self employed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And then there was saddler at Kimberley, Mr Stout. He had some - family living yet. And then 
there was a blacksmith but he's dead, Mr Stubbs. They was all father's friends. More so in doing for the work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And in the other group, those who were better off, you'd get like the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we never saw much of the other groups un
less it was election on or anything of that. That's when we saw them more. They'd come round and see you Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you ever remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we had to treat all people alike. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Or touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 The - the - the Baroness, that was - he was the vicar of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2828014\charrsid10957874 Greazley}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , he was named Baron von Hue. And his wife - used to tell us when we was coming from school if we 
met her on the way she'd say, now - you - you must drop a curtsey to me, and of course we did do. And she used to give us a cutting out of her religious paper. But that was the only time as I ever remembered curtseying to anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But your parents didn't teach you to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No. There were no - no - nothing of that about here in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, and they were both well respected here. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In the district who were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well the colliery owners really more than anything. And then Colonel Rolson at - at Whatnel Hall, but that's pulled down now. He
 was a Colonel in the Army. Retired Colonel, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, quite a lot. When there was anything going off at the church. Or if there was a - say Moorgreen show or anything like that, that's when we saw the most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Why were they considered important?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see - they was very well to do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Because they were wealthy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Wealthy, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about the shopkeepers, you've mentioned one or two people like the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 
saddler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and wheelwright?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Well the shopkeeper you see - mother traded at - latter part at the store, the Co-op, yes. There was the small}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 shopkeepers round about, we used to trade with them to help them along, only ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who do you think that the shopkeepers used to associate with then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - with all the working class round. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - that's been the trouble here. We had a - the Reverend - Galloway, he's not long ago died, you might have seen his wil
l in the Eastwood paper. Reverend A.J. Galloway, he left about thirty-three thousand. He was very good at visiting any denomination. Used to come and see my father and mother often. And he mixed amongst the people. Well - he was supposed to be a confirmed
 bachelor, and then he - all at once he got engaged to Miss Barber, that were the colliery owner's eldest daughter. And - after he married everyone was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 stunned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  at the idea, he was much older than her. She had money. Well they were - he went to - from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Greaseley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 - soon after he was married, and went to Ollerton. Yes. Well he was a Canon there, but you - my brother lived at Mansfield, little boy's father, he lives at Mansfield, they never saw much of Mrs Galloway nowhere. She were never in the limelight. And - 
we often wondered why it was that he married her, why she married }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
. She was a very smart person. But when it come to - when the war was on - the first world war - Mr Galloway's brother or sister was bombed in London. He were - they were bombed. Either o
ne - either brother or sister, I don't know which one it was. Well their uncle left them a huge tea plantation in India and they - he become - he became very rich and that's why we think he married Mrs Barbara, I don't know whether this ought to be said, 
'cos it was so funny he always put himself as a confirmed bachelor. Well his sister, Miss Galloway, formed the - formed the W.I. in 1928 and they was living at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Greazeley}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 vicarage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
, near the church. And - she formed the W.I. and she was very well liked. I went to see her last summer. But she'd had a very bad accident in her car accident, and she - her legs were very bad, and she could only walk }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  two sticks. Well when the election was on here, the general election, Mr James Noone that lives }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  - the far
m at the Castle Farm, he called here to see if I was going to vote and - I wasn't ready and he says, oh by the way. Miss Galloway has been rushed into hospital and she's had a very bad seizure and she - she died after it. Well her will was in the Advertis
er a few weeks ago, just before }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . And she left over twenty-five thousand. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about the teachers, can you remember what the schoolteachers did round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - the one that used
 to teach me, a Miss Whitehead, her father was the headmaster. And - she didn't marry 'til late in life and then there was the butcher's daughter, she was a - schoolteacher. Buy they were very decent - all decent teachers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Oh the farmers mixed with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 each}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  other. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And the employers, like the colliery owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they never seemed to mix with the workers. No. Only just the high nobs as you might call them. Didn't come into limelight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well in - in the Baron's time my brothers and sisters all went to church. It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 when my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  sister Louie, the one a year and a half older than me, when she was five the Baroness came to mother and she said - oh what a l
ovely girl she is. And she said, does she come to my Sunday school? So mother said, well, she said, she's only - she's not five yet. She'll be five in April. Her brother'll bring her along when she's five. Mo of course the Baroness says, oh send her now, 
send her now. That's how she talked. So mother - sent Louie along with me brother Sam and Will and Jack and Ernest and the Baron said - oh he said, who have you got here. And they said, it's my sister, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Louie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Her name was Sarah Louisa but they called her Louie. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And she said, oh, he said, she can't come to the Sunday school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 'til}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 she - 'til after the tea party. Well mother was very annoyed. I can remember it, and so father says, oh well then, if that's it you boys can keep away from church and - they didn't bo
ther to go again. And some of them went to the chapel. Well anyway, my mother started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Louie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 at the chapel. And Albert, Ruth and Albert, we both - we was brought up at the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A bit of a mixture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Well the Baroness came to see mother again and see why the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 boys}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 had stayed away and she says, you ask the Baron, he'll tell you. But mother told her. Oh, and she didn't sort of believe mother. So father told her, he said, you keep out of here and don't come and interfere about my children any mor
e. They just go where they like when they're old enough. And that's how we went to chapel. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where you lived did all the people in your sort of group, the general working class, have the same sort of standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Or would you say there were any different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, there was all sort of working people round here. Yes. Same kind of people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of family would you say would be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 typical}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  of the working classes, how would you describe them generally speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well - some of them that had the schoolteachers they thought they was better off but you see, most of the schoolteachers was either a colliery daughter or a butcher's daughter or a farmers daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You felt sometimes that one group would feel superior or another group did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they may have been but I just can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But there were some distinctions anyway between the working classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh there were some that thought themselves better off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we had quite a few ruffians round about. You see, they got a fathers didn't care and that's where the trouble lay. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were other families described as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Quite respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 As distinct from the rough ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Can you remember if there was a distinction between the sort of jobs people did - like a craftsman and the labourers was there any distinction between the two?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, just the - the men that worked - they had - 
been handed down from their father's you see. Say the wheelwright, his father before him, same with the blacksmith and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they mix fairly well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was no sort of class distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I - no class - no class distinction whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well, yes. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . Yes. Same idea. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . Different persons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No. Mother thought she was one like this - she didn't like to see the women go in the pubs round here, we had a few that used to go in. She was really against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But she would consider herself as belonging to the same general working class group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, she made no distinction among you but they - she let them do as they liked but she made comment sometimes. Just pass a remark.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
possible in those days for people to move from one social group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If he changed his job, a coalminer might become a colliery manager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And move from one social class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see - it's when - as the children grew up they changed. And if they got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 better}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  jobs you could tell - feel a distinction then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember a person who moved up the ladder as it were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Not among our lot. No. You see, when they got better jobs they moved away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They'd move away from the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was this because you were either a miner or a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 farmer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And if you weren't one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  those you had to go somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh quite a few, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Why do you think they were described like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 By - the way they went about and they - the way they helped people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They would help people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 YES. Do any a good turn. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So the term a real lady or a real gentleman could apply to a working class person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. YES. In them - in those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Because it merely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 meant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  they were good to either neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Round about and give help. Yes. You see, in those days people did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  they called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 actions, and didn't look for payment. You'd always find someone willing to go to help anyone that was in distress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, they all came - from different parts. There was one policeman, his daughter and son went to school w
ith us, he was here a long time and then he went to - he would like - he retired - sort - he was on the point of retiring, he went to work for the Co-operative and then - when another policeman came he was elderly with a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was like the local village policeman was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think of him as a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well we had - good policemen here. There was one - policeman, he used to drink himself and he'd never - he never - interfere with a drunkard, but he was very keen on theft. Anyone did any stealing. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did he treat the people generally speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh - like amongst themselves. Yes, he used to come along in here with father and sit and have his wine 'til he was nearly drunk - himself. That was when he was off duty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you as a child ever threatened, I'll call the policeman if you don't do that or don't do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't remember. No. They used to - yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 they\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  frighten the children with it, yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That never happened to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was your home part of your father's job or was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Rented. Yes, all rented. 'Til he bought this. He bought this one in 1915. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When he was renting did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we used to take the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Take the rent to the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you feel anything about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Well it was an old lady that owned the row of houses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Old Lady Farnsworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you feel about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And - she was a very kind old lady. Yes. She passed away in 1919, the week my - son George was born. Yes, she was very old lady.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You felt she was quite a nice person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, and she lived in - next door to the Black Bull here at the farm. Yes. And that was her field wh
ere you go up to the school where all the bungalows are. They call that Farnworth's field today. Yes. Yes. That was her field, belonging the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we were often
 very tight. Especially - when it came November when all the bills came in to be paid yearly. See, the blacksmith's bill, the wheelwright's bill, the saddler's bill and all for the carts and - all for the - work really. That was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 tightest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  time, towards Christmas. And then we went on another year you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh we never - we've never real - was short in a way, we had to go short of clothes as a - as children, we had to wear 'em 'til they was practically wore out but we never wanted if you know what I mean, we'd always got a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill, you can never remember him being out of work can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I can never remember him being ill at all, I - the only 
thing I can remember about father being ill - we was harvesting and the big - the poles up for the stack cloth and he was working for another farmer. He moved the field himself with our won machine and as he was fixing this - stock pole it blew and hit hi
m at back of the head and he fell and broke his ankle. - And that was the only nine week I can ever remember father being ill for a - period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever have to get help from the guardians or the parish or any other charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No not ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which it was shown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, well - there was one - there was one family, the name was Walker, they had the young - one of their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 sons}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , he was more in prison than out. He was really a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 rogue}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the people of the area show any disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They did to him but not to his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 people,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  not to his brothers and sisters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In what way did they show their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they sort of - as we was children we was afraid of him, they used to call him - in fact they used to call him Charlie Peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you would avoid him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Very rough. He wouldn't work. Big strong fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about school, were you given any lessons by one of your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we just went to ordinary everyday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Between four and five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had to be there for nine o'clock - half past eight from home, nine o'clock there. To Belle Vue school, that's where I went. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - came back at - left off at twelve and came back and we had to be there for quarter to two in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And come back at what time in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We left at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What kind of school was it, a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just - no, just an ordinary council school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And it was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And it was a - a board school in those days wouldn't it be. Yes, board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It wasn't boarding was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh no, just a day - they called it a board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was it mixed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. No, boys in one part of the school and girls in another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We used to walk up the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874  fields.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh twenty - no, quarter or an hour, twenty minutes, if we hurried it was quicker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Brothers and sisters and - we went along with other children what was in the same class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 you came home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Oh and all me meals in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I was very fond of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You liked it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I wa
s very sorry 'cos I was a girl, I used to be - I had a lot of illness. I had a lot of illness. And I went - I had one brother and he had - he was same as me, he didn't have much schooling, my brother Ernest. And it was a funny thing, my brother Will was a
 very good scholar - but - we was the only two in those days, if you went a year without a holiday you got some money. Yes. And my brother and Ernest and I were the only two that got it in our family. If you had half a day you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 wouldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  - and they were so pleased that I could go to school for a full year, that was after 19 - I was in standard two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874  for two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 years and a half, I wouldn't go up, 'cos I was ill and missed the exams and I could have gone up because I - anyway, out of standard two into standard three,
 I got the money. And I went into standard four and I was only in standard four a month - and I had rheumatic fever. And - I was very ill for a long time, in fact I called myself an Eskimo, I was wrapped up in wadding from head to foot. And I left school 
-
 they made me leave when I was eleven. Doctor wouldn't allow me to go. And I worried about it and I kept saying to mother, I'm going to school. She said, now you know you - they won't have you. Doctor's orders. And I used to call the doctor when he came, 
called in to see how I was, I did used to carry on. And he said, I worked too hard and I worked me brain too much and it wasn't good for me and he definitely stopped me from going. But I beat him, when I was fourteen I went six years to night school.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He couldn't stop you going there could he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No, and I - it was dictation and composition and sums and all that, arithmetic, I'm very good at arithmetic. And - anyway - then they brought cookery on with that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 
But I had a dictionary, I had a cookery book, I had two lovely reading books, Agatha's Husband and Love's Sacrifice, and then I had a work box and - Enquire Within upon everything, that was it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And I went 'til I was eighteen. 'Til I was twenty I mean, and I used to go on me bike and we used to have
 to go to Eastwood for the cooker, Albert Street school. But - I meant having my schooling. But I - I - I didn't - I didn't enjoy like I did at the day school. I missed from eleven to fourteen, you see, you could go in for your labour exam when you were t
welve. Which my - some of my brothers and sisters did. But I wanted to get in to get in for that but I were very good at arithmetic. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you were a girl at school how did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I was very fond of all the teachers. I got on well because I was a good scholar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the teachers emphasise particular things as important in life, like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh they used to teach us manners, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Very good at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
You see, some of the teachers were rather elderly and they married late in life but they was very good and very decent teachers. Yes. Same with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 boys\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What would happen when you did something the teacher disapproved of, how would they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well some of them have to stay in and write lines. Just the same as they do today in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were the girls treated the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. You see, there - there was all lady teachers for the girls, and men teachers for the boys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 For what sort of offences would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well if you was talking when you shouldn't talk or - stay in and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 do}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  so many lines. But I was never sort of punished really, I don't know, they used to say, oh teacher likes you because you're good - we had some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 dances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  in the class remember and if you tried to help them they wouldn't let you but - we had very decent teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes. They were very keen on us going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well there were nothing to visit in those days. They never - nothing doing. No, not like the parent teachers, no, nothing of tha
t. No, no - no one - nothing - you had to bring your work home for your mother to see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents meet the teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't - sometimes the teachers should call and tell mother how I were getting on with being one that was ill 
a lot. I think if ever was anything going I caught it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, they came - oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see, if they was a bit backward }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  had to sit on a row to themselves. And the good scholars had to sort of help them, though when you got in the playground they - took it out of you. Think as - oh why should you show m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 e up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and - just cause a bit of annoyance there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well one or two used to be a bit rough, like both girls and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, there didn't seem to be so many in thos
e days that was left out of anything really. After - I left school there was - they had what they called a special class at Bow Vale. And there's a young woman in Bowman Street now, she's about - she's over fifty - she was in this class, where they was a 
bit dull you see. That was the only thing I can remember. As regards anything in that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, I left when I was eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You would have stayed on if you could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 wouldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I should have gone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  after when I was better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you did go to part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 To evening classes for six years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you went to evening classes from when you were fourteen to when you were twenty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. I had six years at night school. And enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You regretted having that gap in your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Any other regrets about education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I think going to night school helped me a lot. Yes, in every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And the day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, I - I was always very fond of going to school. None of ours - what they used to call in those days they used to say you were capping school, not going you know, they
 used to call it capping school, if you stayed away. Then there used to be a gentleman come round to see why.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Why did they call it capping school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - if you had a holiday - if you stayed away out of school, and some of the mothers didn't kn
ow they hadn't been to school 'til the - the man came that used to come and inquire why they wasn't at school. They always called it capping. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 You\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  capping school, he'd capped school today. That's how they used to put it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Means he's skipped it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. Just played truant. Of course they didn't say played truant in those days. Then there was old gentleman, he wasn't very nice, a Mr Holton, he used to go round and when we saw him we used to say, I wonder who old Holton's after today. That was just in
 the - children's talk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you were at school did you have a part time job or any way of earning any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Only just taking milk out for father, that was all. We all sort of brought up to have to work at home while we was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was your first full time job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What - in education do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you left school what was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh, just taking milk out, milking - on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you worked on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you worked with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And worked - helped mother indoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you worked for your father in the milk business then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to have to - fetch the cows up from the field. And help to milk them. And retail it night and morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of hours did you worked.?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I was working all day then, cleaning cows out, helping on the farm. Then helping mother indoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So it'd be ten or twelve hours a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was Sunday any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we just had to - we all - we didn't - I wasn't allowed to do much on a Sunday besides - just do the milking and taking the milk out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Saturday was a hard day, we had to work hard Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there a half day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Nos. No half days in them days. You had to work just 'til the work was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I generally used to have a week away - a week away at either one of me brothers or sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I - I just had pocket money. Yes, pocket money, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you feel that you got a fair wage for your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I got what mother and father could spare. That's how I took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you didn't have to give any to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were living and working in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I got on well with everyone, I'm well liked in every way, in fac
t I'm all - I'm called more by my maiden name today round here than what I am Mrs Robinson. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you feel about your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I enjoyed it, I loved the farm work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your job didn't alter your attitude to school did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't have any other part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No. None whatever. I used to nurse children for people, just to set them at liberty, not as a matter of being a - not working, not earning. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just ordinary housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would you have preferred a type of occupation, any sort of career?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - I - no, I don't think so. 'Cos I was married and got the children so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't serve an apprenticeship did you, or a training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No way whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you feel that employers and workers and had the same sort of interests or different at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see, with never being employed by anyone, only father, I never thought about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It was a rather different situation wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers, some people say that in those days there was a great division betwe
en trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see, those that learnt the trade there was a big difference. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there a division between them, do you think they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 divided}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well of course the one would have the - learning o
f the work and the other had just to carry on with anything he could do, that's how it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way? It wouldn't for you because you were in the family anyway weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, because, you see, I just had to just carry on and do what I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did it change with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, because you see I was left - the last one to be at home with father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You've already said that Sunday was spent differently, you went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I just went to vote, I didn't do anything as regards - joining politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were married before 1918 weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were telling me earlier about how you spent your spare time, did you continue to spend your spare time in 
the same way after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, I used to go bike riding and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Chapel and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh was allowed to go if we wanted to go anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 To what sort of places?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well, if you wanted to go to a friend's house or - when the pictures came if we could go to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 With girl friends. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you make any new friends at these sort of times, when you were going out on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, you see with living here all me life I just - stuck to the old friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we were allowed to bring them home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any special friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I had quite a few, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of places would you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well used - we used to all go - five of us used to go biking together and we' go to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your parents would meet these friends of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, yes, quite all right. They used to come and call for us. Every one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But your parents would expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, they wanted to know where we was going and - we had to be back for nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Twenty - I was married in 1915, I was twenty-three I think. Twenty-three and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How long had you known your husband?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I knew him when he was fifteen - when I was fifteen. He was four years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you'd known him for seven and a half years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
And then - he went away - he lived at a farm at Watnall, called Rook Resting Farm, he lived there a farm labourer. He - he lived at - he came from Long }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Lemington}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  near Newark. Yes, do you know Long Lemington. Yes, through on the Long Way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It's just off the A1 isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, it's about six mile from Newark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well he came - he lived at a farm and the - I was very friendly with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 
farmer\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  daughters. A Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Hatwood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , lived at Roo
k Resting Farm, top }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 end}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 N}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
ew Road, Watnell, and - he lived there - he were there for a year and then he went home again. Then when I was eighteen he came - before I was eighteen he came to live at the farm where Shorts Coal - that colliery is. And that's
 how I got in with him again there. But we didn't go out much together, I went with another young man. But I didn't care for him and I went back to the old one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you save up money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I got quite a nice bit of money before I married, I used to have pigs you see and feed them myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your parents help you in setting up your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they - they helped me with - I used to have a bit more pocket money when I got older. And then having pigs and fow
ls myself that's where I made my money - on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh from when I was - twenty - nearly twenty. November as I was twenty in the December.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you would be engaged for three years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just an ordinary wedding, we was married at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 Greazely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  church. And just had an ordinary wedding at home because the war was on. You see, my husband then, he left the colliery, he left in 1912 he left the farm and went into the colliery. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 worst}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  day's work we - I always say that he ever did. He never - he was a good farm - would have been a good farmer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you describe the wedding then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we just - went - we had a brake - we had a - a brake and a - we did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 n
\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  have a car, I was saying we didn't have a car - just for us, but we had - we had a pair of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 gr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 ys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 and a - you know, what they used to have. Yes. And - but that was all for the - big lot, it went twice that did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It made two journeys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It was a family wedding at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. At - at Lever church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And there were other guests invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go away for a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. Mother wasn't too well. But - that was the tenth of July and at August Bank Holiday we went away 
for a week to Long Bennington and we went out every day. Yes. We had the honeymoon then really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you live after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Number eleven Baldwin Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In Newthorpe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 For how many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 19 years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you live them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I came to live at 193 Main Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was in the '30's then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was in - 1938.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How old was your husband when you married him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was - he was - twenty-eight in the June as we was married in the July.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So he was just twenty-eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, it made it four - he was four years and a half older than me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was his job when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He worked in the - he was a - worked on the conveyors in the colliery. A miner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He worked on the conveyors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he have other jobs before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he was a collier right up to his death. He used to help the farmers when they was harvesting, at night, you know with the - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was for part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Just the extra bit of pocket money, yes. Well he was a good - he was a farmer really, he was a - a good one for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 building}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  stacks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But basically in his working life he was a coal miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She was a miner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He died in a mining accident didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes, he hurt his knee and he was under Doctor - he was under Doctor Miles. And - they brought him home in the ambulance on the sixteenth of August.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What years wax that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 1934. Yes. And
 he - he was bad from the - from the Thursdays they brought him home at quarter to four and he passed away - midnight Sunday night. We called the doctor but he'd passed away before the doctor got there. And of course I wasn't very well pleased with him}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1916474\charrsid10957874 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  he'd got his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 stethoscope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  in his hand and - of course that's going on there isn't it. I told him - when he came in the room I said, it's all over doctor. And I says, you've got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 
stethoscope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  in your hand, why didn't you use it? And he didn't know what to sa
y. He'd never examined him. I wasn't a bit worried about - compensation, I'd lost a good husband. And it was a very sad blow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He did some harvest work in the evenings during the season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you yourself do any work after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No. Only what I helped my mother for - I came to help mother and father. Yes. I didn't do any - for no wages, just to help her - she was getting on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did your husband feel about his work down the pits, did he like it, did he think it was a good job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well he - he enjoyed it because he was with some good workmen, there was ten of them working together. But - I often think he was - his heart lay in the farm. We should have gone to Canada in 1919 but - his mother died and 
I helped look after her and - I didn't like leaving my mother so he - my nephew wrote to see if we'd go and he said, I'll just leave it to you. So with that we never went and I rued the day in one way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. I had a daughter born on the twenty-fifth of April, 1916, when the zeppelins were coming over. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And then - yes, two year and eleven month after that I had a son. On the third of March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That would be 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, 1919, after the war was over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. You see there was no nurses or anything at that time, not round here. We had to have the midwife and the doctor. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you know what to expect in childbirth, I suppose being in a big family you knew all about it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes. Yes. Well I was - I was really wonderful because - at the time I told you about having the - rheumatic fever, it affected my heart and I was very bad, I had an enlarged heart. - That's why I couldn't go to school. Y
es, yes, and - the doctor said I mustn't do this and I mustn't do the other. But - I've al - although I say it, I've always had good will power, and I wouldn't give in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you get on in the actual confinement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - wonderful. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 I had my 
daughter - the doctor in Northwood, that was Doctor Miles- Doctor Miles was Doctor Northwood's partner. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
And Doctor Northwood had a brother that was a partner to him and he was at Eastwood and Doctor Northwood at Kimberley. Well Doctor Sam Northwood went to
 live at Mapperley at Nottingham. And - he died rather sudden, he used to like his drink. I'm not saying anything more of that to go on the - I could tell you after that. And anyway, when my daughter was born the doctor sat on my bed and he said to the ol
d
 lady, 'cos her daughter lives down the bottom of the road, Miss Lowe, he said to the old lady, he said, I'll give all the money I've got Mrs Gaunt, this was to my mother and this old midwife, if my brother Sam could see this child. Because, he said, I ne
ver thought she'd live to be married and have a baby it's astonishing. And he - he - that was the words Doctor Northwood said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was he there at the actual birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he came after. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who was there at the actual birth then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 mother and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  this midwife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your own mother and a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. She was very clever but she was not certified but we spoke for the doctor you see before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband do anything during the birth or was he away at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh he was at work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How soon were you out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well in those days they kept you in bed 'til ten days. Yes. Yes. The days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you manage while you were in bed with the young baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well my - I had a friend came and stayed with me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did she stay for all those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Stayed for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6969254\charrsid10957874 fortnight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and then my sister-in-law came for a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did they do, the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They - they did all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 housework}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and looked after me and I'd got to take care but - I was wonderful really, I mean - but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 didn't do anything for a month but I - they thought - well, what I'd gone through and then having this baby, well I fed the baby myself. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't have a nurse as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No nurse whatever. No. No nurse whatever. There was no nurse in the district then, only a district nurse would help elderly people. No - midwifery nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You fed your own baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Oh - then I had another baby. I had one ten years after. I - o
n the tenth of May, when the - can you remember the big strike 1926. Well he - he was born on the tenth of May. When everything was at a standstill. It was funny. There was - he was born just on the tenth of May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You breast fed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you enjoy feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes. Right to nine months. I fed the second baby too. And the third.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you didn't have any difficulty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No difficulty whatever over my confinements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If you needed any advice about bringing the baby up who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If the baby was asleep and it was time for its feed did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 wake}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  it up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, not in those days. No, he used - she used - they was all very good, it was wonderful, I could tell they was go
ing to waken by my breast myself. Yes. You see, my mother had experienced all that and she explained.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If the baby cried before the normal feeding time would you then feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I used to give it warm water. Not over feed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How long would you let it go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well about four hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember about what age it was when you first gave him solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - just after six month I used to give them rice pudding and - anything like that. Just soft foods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We're talking now about your first baby aren't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And we used to have - give them - I used to give them rusks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mona. Yes. Just Mona.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874  wanted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 the baby at about what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well between nine and ten month. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Gradually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - it was really, yes, for the first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the baby seem to mined being weaned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, no, because she began to eat - and it went off - it was all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 At that time do you think it did any harm to a baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh she was a very good baby really. They used to say you mustn't let them cry but - of course she cried when it was - when she was three months old she had a lump come in her gum and the doctor - aid he thought it was a tooth comin
g through. So we had to just send for him but however - the lump went down but she did cut her teeth early. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever find it necessary to punish her if she was naughty?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She was a very good girl and the marvellous reports that she had from school was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How much did your husband have to do with the children when they were very small babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh he'd always hold them and help me with them. Yes, very good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He'd give them a bath and those sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. When they got big enough for me to leave he used to look after them then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would he change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, he's done that a time or two.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Played with them, put them to bed when he was on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. When I've been out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Look after them at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. You see, there was seven years and two months between the boys. Yes. Thought we - thought we was clever you know and thought we'd got as many as we could keep and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But the girl and the first boy were just about within three years of each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Two year eleven months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you know how much your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, he always put his pay packet on the table. Yes. And - when he wanted pocket money he used
 to take what he wanted but it was not a great deal 'cos in them days - we didn't have much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you'd have the bulk of it anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I always had his pay packet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he used to discuss with you how the money should be spent?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. He
 used to leave it to me and he used to tell people when they talked about housekeeping and that, he said, when my wife can't manage I'll take over. And that was his one saying. But he always trusted me. And I trusted him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many rooms were in the house at Baldwin Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had - the scullery and the living room and the front room and three bedrooms. No bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I - my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 niece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  came to live with me in 1920 but she was only with me two months while she could get a house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't have any paid help in the house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you make the clothes for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to - some underclothes but not their best clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But mending you would do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I did a lot of mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have mainly new or secondhand clothes for the children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh generally new ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 From the Co-op or - the big shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
From the Co-op, yes. And I was a big - my husband was a big Labour man you know. So was I. But we - mind you, my father turned Labour in the end. Oh yes. I meant to tell you that the other day and I - it just lipped me m
ind. Oh yes. Oh my - my husband went out meetings and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So that be before he retired or after, your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Father. He - before he retired. Oh yes. When the Labour movement came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Before the first world war then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. oh yes. Oh he knew he - we told - he told us he'd turned, he - he went to Labour, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband help with jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He used to wash up for me if I wasn't up to the mark any time, he'd always help me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he do any cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Only - he could just do the breakfast more than anything. You see, when - I was first married mother used to come down if - I wasn't very often ill. It was funny thing, after my daughter I didn't have the doctor for ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So he was fairly handy about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, oh he was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he do decorating and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he didn't do any decorating. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who did that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had a friend that used to come and do it. An ordinary collier man but he was very good at decorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You said he used to help with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did he used to help them after they were babies, undressing them and reading to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, yes, yes. And he'd always sit with them when they were having their music lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They had music lessons did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, Mona played the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You had a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I've got a piano now. I've still - still got it. Yes, she learned - she had - exams. And he used to time them and he 
felt - helped them a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He used to encourage her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Although he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  musical himself he knew the time and he timed same with my son, they - and Mona used to play the piano and George the violin, at concert and everywhere. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He would look after them if you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And he would take them out himself would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. And you see, with being a big family of us - I was called way, I couldn't tell you how many hospitals I've been and visited through - my bro
ther Sam, he got hurt in 1930, my brother Ernest got killed at Broadsworth colliery when he was forty-seven, in 1929. My brother Sam got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  back hurt, we thought it was broke, he was in the hospital two years. At - Blackwell colliery. Yes, Blackwell colliery and he was in Chesterfield Royal Infirmary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you've got a lot of misfortune from the pits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh I have. Oh yes. Yes. Yes. And we'd - accidents too and then my other brother got the coal - my brother William, he got the coal cutting machine t
hrough his ankle. And his wife was in London with her mother at East Ham, her mother was very ill. And I had had him for a month. He couldn't get out of bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your own children do any work around the house, any household }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 tasks}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh the - my da
ughter used to wash pots and do all that and the boy - George, my second boy, he used to go - come to the farm and take milk out for them, morning and night, before he went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What time did you put your children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they used to
 go between seven and eight. Earlier when they were younger but when they got a bit - they - with the two being - same age, and they both had separate rooms. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was it usual for them to go by themselves or did one of you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - they always went by themselves. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And they had their own separate bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You and your husband had the other bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There wasn't a bathroom was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who where did you have a - bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had - used to have to have it in front of the fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Saturday night for the children and then of course when my husband was on afternoons I used to have my bath. He had afternoons one week and days another. And then he had his bath every Saturday night last thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When did the children have clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Sunday morning. And we - yes, and if needed in the week they had them again but - not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And where were meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we never - we had a parlour but we never used that for anything, only just if friends came - with a piano you know, the music.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You might have something to eat in the parlour if it was a special thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, just on trays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Where did you cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In the living room. Open stove. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It - about eight o'clock. Yes. Before the children went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you normally all together then, all the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 My husband had - would have gone to work if he was on days and then he would have a breakfast with us if he was on afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So if your husband was on days he'd be gone out anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. He used to go out before six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How would he get on for his first meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh he'd get him to - he always - I never got up with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He got himself something to eat before he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. He used to pack his snap as we a call it, pack his snap at night and everything was all ready for him to help himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have anything different on certain days, was Sunday breakfast any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we generally - we ran on the old fashioned - sometimes we had porridge and then we had the egg and bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Right away 'til the war, 'til you couldn't use the flour you know. Always made my own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I never made any wine because father used to make a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your father used to make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't think we made any kind of medicines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about bottled fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to bottle fruit at the Women's Institute. During the war. We had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. We had a - a cook come from Brackenhurst Farm, I don't know if you've heard of that. Well then - from Shire Hall these people used to come and give demonstrations y
ou know and - we used to have the tins come and do all our own - we used to use the machine and bottle fruit and tin tomatoes. We did a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you grow any vegetables and fruit yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I - I had allotment garden. Yes. Yes. We had allotment, I kept it on six years after my husband died. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you grow any vegetables and fruit there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Gooseberry trees and - then potatoes and cabbage, all vegetables. Yes. But I had a cousin that used to come and help to dig, 'til my boys were able to dig it. Then I gave it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about tinned fruit or dried fruit, did you have any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to buy a lot of dried fruit to make the - jam, apricot jam. Just that kind of dried fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But not vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes, we always had fowls. Yes. And pigs. Yes. You see, we used to keep the pigs with father here. Yes. And it's funny thing - in 1914 - that was when the war broke out - we went to Long Bennington, we always went to his ho
me first week in August and at the Manor at Long Bennington used to have a garden party. And - 'course me and my husband went to this garden party, it was - first time I'd ever been to the garden party, I'd been to Long Bennington before, and we went to t
h
is garden party and they had a big blackboard with rings on, kind of quoits you know. You know what I mean? Piece of round leather. Well there - on this blackboard there was all circles. And - it was tuppence a go. So - of course there was some of the men
 
that knew my husband, they said, come on Fred and have a go. And - oh he says, I'll have a go. And of course he chucked a shilling down. He said, no change, I'll - have several goes, only tuppence a go. And they said, what about your wife? Oh he says, she
'
s not my wife yet. She's my young lady. So - oh he says, come and have a go miss. And I says, well are strangers allowed? Funny thing that I should say that. Oh he says, you paid your money to come in the garden party, it's open to anybody. I had one go, 
t
uppence. After my husband had spent his shillings worth. And I got the highest number. And do you know, there were a lot of farmers, farm labourers, they'd got thirteen, eleven and ten but I held the fourteen to the finish. And - anyway, the - the prize w
a
s a pig. An eight week old pig. And Mr Bingham, he was a big farmer at Long Bennington, and he gave this pig - well at that time you couldn't move a pig about Nottinghamshire because of the - foot and mouth disease. And I had to leave it at my husband's h
ome for a month, twenty-eight days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was round about 1913 or '14 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 This was 1914, the year the war broke out. The year - the day it was declared really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was foot and mouth in the county at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was - there w
as restrictions because there'd been - there had been foot and mouth disease - far distant but it was - you couldn't move an eight weeks old pig only by license to the market or anything like that. So it was - anyway, it was kept there for twenty-eight da
ys and father and I and my - husband to be, we went and fetched it back with pony and trap. Went one day and come back the next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who looked after the pig then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 My husband's father. Oh I looked after it when I got it home. Oh yes. Because we'd - w
end got pigs you see. And we lived at the farm at that time. It was at Moorgreen. But I - my pig went in a place to himself. And wasn't I pleased. I fed him and - we put eight pounds - when I sold him, I sold him to the Co-op. I says to father, you're not
 
going to kill my pig. We used to kill a lot of pigs and sell to the milk customers, when we lived on the farm. And I said, my pig's going to the Co-operative and I'm going to see it weighed. And I went and saw it weighed, and I drew eight pounds seven and
 threepence. And I thought I was a millionaire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you were in Baldwin Street you kept a bit of livestock then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I still have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874  fowls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And my husband too. And I looked after them after he died. And then we had pigs here with father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But your father looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Well - my husband used to help him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How many times a week did you eat meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see - it was a different price, I mean, the 
- oh - oh yes, we used to have a joint on a Sunday. Perhaps two or three pounds - a joint and then we used to have stewing meat on a Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you'd have it two or three times a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we had chops. Sometimes we had liver instead of chops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
No. No. No, my - we didn't want any of that did they used to have during the war. They - no, they called it the bully beef, it was - corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But you didn't have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. We didn't fancy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever get any extra from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well, you see I was at home, we didn't do any poaching after we left the farm. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever have to go short of food so that your children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, no, we was never short
. And then - the 1926 strike just took all our savings, but - you see, a lot of men went out cropping, you've heard of that I expect. Yes. Getting the coal from gardens. They did all kinds of - they come to dig our field. On the surface, what they called 
outcropping. Yes, they - the men. But my husband wouldn't join them. And of course it was very hot summer, 1926, and he said, no, he says, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 we\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  on strike. He said, it's; you see, the railways and everything were stands till. I Just for one day. And some fo
r one week and he said, while you're outcropping and keeping factories going, he says, we shall never get in, he says, I shall go to work the moment the pits open. And of course, it was open - then it was - strike was on a many weeks, my John was born on 
t
he tenth of May, that was my baby was born, say he couldn't have been worse but I'd - couldn't get a pram for love or money. Couldn't buy one Then I had to finish up with a Tansad. We did get one in the end. But he was quite three months old. A Tansad pra
m.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Rather a low one, a very dear one it was. Very dear to what my daughter's was when we had her. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That strike dragged on a bit didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh it did and we had - we drew - we didn't owe a penny, we didn't have to
 borrow, and we just had a few pounds left when he went to work again. But we just went without - what we could go without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We were talking earlier about the way you had to behave when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you were having your own family, did you allow your children to take at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, no. They was brought up very - same as - similar to ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could they choose what they wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, we never - now we'd got to have it, either that or nothing, but - if my children didn't like a thing we didn't press them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So they could leave some uneaten if they didn't want it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, if they - I didn't give - used to give them a lot to waste. If they didn't care for it, well, they didn't have it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about things like passing stuff up the table and that, did they used to have to ask for, say, the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If they wanted anything they used to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about for a second helping, could they always ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes. If there was any for them they could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were they taught to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Proper way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. They were very good mannered I will say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you allow them to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, when they had a meal they'd go to finish and they'd go to say their grace and get down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When did the members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When we all left together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 All those who were present for the meal would sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Of course the baby - baby in the high chair. I had a high chair, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the children have their own special places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And my husband, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who was the meal served by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 e. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When the children were too young to feed themselves you say you had a high chair?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A high chair. Yes. And I fed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When would they join in the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, when they could manage to help to feed themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way and a wrong way to bring up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well yes, I taught them to be honest - and the same as we was taught really. I had no difficulty in that. I'd no difficu
lty in them coming in to go to bed or going to bed. And they was always well - always well behaved at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband share the same attitude as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You both had a like mind towards the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We didn't have any quarrel over the children. It wasn't a matter of - I'll ask mother, I'll ask dad, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you discuss it with your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How you think they should be brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh only mother and this old midwife, she used to come and see us quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But your mother was available anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, with being close to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often did you see your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh every day. Yes. I used to come up and see - when I got married I had sort of two homes, I had to come and help mother 'cos she was getting on then, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh in lots of ways. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you and she have the same sort of ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well she'd tell me how - what she used to do and of course I used to sort of do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She was a very nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did she live locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, she was at Long Bennington. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It was quite some way away wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Yes. And she used to - my husband's father was a farm labourer and she used to ways for the Manor. And then I'm sorry to say she - had gangrene. And she pa
ssed away when she was sixty-two. Be - that was in 1923, before my last boy was born. When we had George, on the third of March 1919, she came over and she was very sorry that we'd called him George. But I - when I had my first baby I told my husband if i
t was a girl I would have the choice, and that we agreed on that. Well I had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 niece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 that went out to Canada, I'll show you her photograph - went out to Australia, and she was only three. And - mother said to me, if you have a little girl would you like to 
call her Mona? I said, mother that's what I'm going to do because my sister went to Australia - her husband got killed on the North London Railway in 1912. I went up off a holiday on the Saturday and he got killed the next morning. So I got a big shock. A
n
d - he was a very nice fellow, very tall, he'd been on the line eighteen year and never had an accident. But he was cut up to pieces at Clapham Junction, you've heard of that. Yes. And I stayed with my sister five week but I never ought to have done and t
h
en I had a break down on the following February. Well she stuck it - father had her brought home here and got a little house for her and then she would - she would go to Australia, she went out on the government, left one boy at home with my brother at Ma
n
sfield, took this little girl, three, with her. And - she went out in the far bush under the government as housekeeper. But on the way out to Australia she - the chief steward was very good to her. Helped her with her luggage and everything. And for two y
ears she worked as housekeeper and she corresponded with this - this - this steward. And when he retired off the sea - they married. And he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  over a tremendous big building at Sidney Harbour. And - of course they was married and - you see, 
this big building, it was like - wool merchants on the floor, skin merchants so all - every so many merchants and it - of course they had good money and my sister had to look after the cleaners. So with taking this little girl out we called my daughter Mo
na. That's how she got her name. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I - with buying the piano, I so wanted my daughter to learn the piano. And she did do and she was a good girl with her less
ons. But we - she - passed so many exams but we didn't let her keep on. We thought with her schooling she'd got plenty on. So she - she had - about seven years learning. She's a beautiful player.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh, she was a very good gi
rl. George, that's the second boy, he used to think he could go and do just what the other boy did, going down to the brook you know and - coming all wet with sludge and that. We wasn't ever so strict, we let them play with them because going to the same 
school you've sort of got to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any problems with them regarding affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh we was all affectionate. Yes. Yes. And then John you see, with being - George was seven years and two months and Mona was ten - but he thought the world of him. She's a very nice fellow. That's the one on the sideboard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about safety of your children, did you feel you had to do anything special for them in regard to safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. We had a range for the fireguard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And traffic wasn't a problem in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, there were no traffic - not near so much traffic, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You never had any problems regarding feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, they used to have same as we had and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you want them to share any worries they might have with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we hadn't - in my home we had no worries, me and my husband. It was other - it was relatives that - where the trouble lay. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How did you want your children to behave towards you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well to do that was right, be very affectionate - in 
every way. My youngest son was only eight when his father died but he - used to go to the garden, he copied his father in every way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When the children were young did you ever manage to leave them so you could go out, you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we - of course mother used to have them. That's - always someone in - we never left them on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When would you be able to go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - we used to go to the Newark show, you know, there's one in for - it used to be three 
days show. And we went to the Royal Show several times. Of course my husband used to have to have a holiday for that and then we left them in care of mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But it was only on special occasions like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And your mother was there anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Oh they came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, they never did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort or things did you bring them up to consider to be important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well, to be honest and - not to tell lies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you tell them to hit back if they were hit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I - I used to tell them they must stick up for themselves. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there any other children that you discouraged your own children from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well - my children didn't mix up with any of them in a way of speaking, they didn't just trouble about them. Because there was such a lot of rough ones both in Stanford Street and Baldwin Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If your children did something that you disapproved of what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh they had to go to bed same as what we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was a sort of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who would give them this punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well, I used to - I used to give it to them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just by telling them to go up to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I said, well now you've been naughty, you've done what's wrong, now go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often do you think this might happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh it was very rare. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was it ever done by their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I think he left that to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was there any particular occasion when you had to take a firm hand with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't remember. I'd no real trouble with them at all as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would you say your children received their ideas about how to behave from both of you, or you or your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I think from both of us really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You didn't go to work after you were married and had children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we used to - they used to bring their friends in. I've had as many as thirty-three at one birthday party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, they used to bring presents when they came along, just friends, children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And things to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would it be different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, we always had - plenty of good things for them. And have games for the, 'cos you see father had the field and if it was fit they used to finish up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So there'd be like a little party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Play ball or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and your children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well if we didn't go to Long Bennington we always came here. Yes. Yes. Yes. But my brothers, they couldn't come with all living away and - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 A piano. And two violins. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your daughter was taught to play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who played the violins then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 George. Yes, the second boy. And I started John on the piano but he would not have it. He didn't care for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So the music in your house would be basically from Mona your daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever have a sing-song together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we had friends in too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You had friends in to have a sort of musical evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you play games with the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we played a lot of games with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, they'd play ludo or anything like that.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, they had a lot of reading books. Yes. As they grew older they had different books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well they had - they had a comic but we used to have an evening paper. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have a morning paper as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have magazines about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, we only had the - magazine from the church. We didn't have no magazine - no books. Had a church - every month. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you belong to the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, we never belonged - there was no library in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children, you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If they wanted us to read anything out of their books we used to read it to them. Either me or him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever read to your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he could read himself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were the children taken out visiting to friends or relations or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, they used to often go and - my sister that lived in London, her husband was in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 Metropolitan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  Police, she used to 
have them - she used to have my - my daughter, my sister's daughter and my brother's - this is the one that died in the - doctor's surgery - and they had a little girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So they would go there every summer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who would take them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
They'd go by train. We used to put - I used to put them on at Midland Station at Nottingham, and - as soon as they arrived my sister used to send a telegram - home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your sister would meet them off the train in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She'd meet them off the train. Yes. We never had no - trouble with them travelling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were they taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes. They used to go to Eastwood with us when we - or to Nottingham. You see, in those days you - we had the trams, in - there were trams first then buses. We - we used to go on train sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the trams used to come as far as Eastwood then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh to Ripley. The tram - from Nottingham to Ripley. Yes. And they wasn't put down 'til - 19 - was it 1912. Yes, 1912. And the - when the trams were laid to Nottingham. From Ripley to Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you had a fairly good service then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes. 'Til you got to a junction and it was either one tram had got to go back or the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, he used to take them out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You used to go to shows and that at Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Mainly you used to go out to shows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was in the summer?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And then you see Moorgreen show, that used to be in September but today it's in August. These days it's at August time. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever go away for a holiday in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we went to Skegness, we went to Mablethorpe. For a week. Week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Regularly every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We went - well - twice I was disappointed because my mother was ill, so I couldn't go. We went - quite a few times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You went to Skegness and Mablethorpe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, that was the nearest - with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You went there because it was the nearest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You all went did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes, we had a week off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What sort of activities did you get up to on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we'd play on the sands with them and go on the roundabouts you know, just - ordinary holiday. But we did go to Lon
don quite a lot for a holiday for a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You went to London as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I used to go with the children, my husband came for the weekend. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He'd stay at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Because of the work, he couldn't come from his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Could you tell me how you spent your Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well he used to generally be in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well if we - when he come home we used to go to the pictures. First house. And that was our - outing every week really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about Sunday, how would you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
We all - the Sunday - they went to Sunday school and then I used to go - my husband and me used to go to chapel. And when the girl was old enough we didn't take them at night, when she was old enough to look after
 the two boys. Or they'd come and stay with mother if mother wasn't able to go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you and the children wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we always had our best clothes, yes. We always had best clothes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you think it wrong to work or to enjoy yourself on a Sunday or did you think it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well my husband was rather strict, he wouldn't do anything in the farm work for anybody, it didn't matter whether it was harvest what. He liked Sunday as Sunday. He'd always been brought up to that. And my father, he was - he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 a religious man but he wouldn't have anything done on a Sunday more than could be helped. And he wouldn't do any mowing or leading or anything of that. Same as they had to do during the war. But he wouldn't - no. He did observe Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your children play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, no, they used to read books when they come from Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you attend a place of worship yourself, you went to chapel didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well we used to go in the afternoon if there was anything special, very often in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Sunday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, and - and they dropped this Sunday afternoon service off in the second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you'd go at least once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Every - every evening, Sunday evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It was the Baptist chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband go with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He used to go with me unless it was anything to see to the children, he'd stay with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I was in the choir, I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you were in the choir until you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Not after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to help them at - concerts or anything special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did the chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I don't - not in our time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What other activities did they do at the chapel then, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 concerts}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well used to have concerts at - purpose to uphold the chapel, to keep it going and - we always had a good mini
ster, but not a - a stationery minister. Just a lay preacher or a minister -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did they go to any of the adult or family services at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Quite a few. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was grace said at meals in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Sometimes. Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were your children taught to say their prayers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh they always said their prayers before they got into bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Who taught them that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to taught - teach them, then they used to kneel at side of the bed when they got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you take an interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I used to go to the Labour meetings sometimes but I always went to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What were your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - to help one another and to be honest more than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you support the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. All my life. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was strong Labour. Yes. Yes. He used to go to all the meetings. There were any big meetin
gs. I don't know if you ever heard about a man named Mr Cook, have you ever heard of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 , Cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He was - he wasn't in this area but he was for the colliers - that was like in the 1926 strike. But he was a very good man but he died 
rather sudden, he took ill, he wasn't old when he died. No, you see - this area was what they called the Brockster division, it was a very strong Labour movement. Yes. Well when they changed to Rushcliffe division it's just split up. That's the trouble.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They're changing it again, did you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I hope they will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 They're taking Eastwood into this division.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Into this division? Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you or your husband }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 vote}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we voted ever since we was able to have votes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He normally voted anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. He voted - the same with the local elections too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And he voted for which party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he was always for the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But he didn't feel under any pressure from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh no, no, if he - he thought - his way was this, if
 there was a good man put up, but he generally voted - you see, we had Mr Seymour Cox here for years and years. He was the M.P. and he was a cripple. And everybody voted for him round here, always got in with a big majority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Were you a member of a political party at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I used to go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 Greazely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  Labour party. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever work for one of them at the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I never did anything to do in the election but we used to have - whist drives to help the funds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about your husband, did he take an active part in the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he never did anything - no, not in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 So your activities other than at elections times was having whist drives to help the Labour party funds?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you and your husband were not doing your various jobs of work how did you spend your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - really and truly we would work the garden than anywhere. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Not in the week. Not very often. No. Because I was always out at whist drives or something of that, he had to stay with the children.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You went out one at a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When did your husband get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - he was on shifts, yes, aftern
oons and days. You see, when he was on days he used to get home about quarter to four in those days when he was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He would spend most evenings at home would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. And in the - when it was gardening time he did his garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did either of you go to clubs or institutes or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 I didn't - no, I - I just belonged the W.I., I didn't go to anything doing - not - not with the pub - not to the pubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 But you belonged to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  Institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, just belonged to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  Institute in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Once a month. The second Thursday of every month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did your husband have any regular activities like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, he didn't join anything. He used to go to a lot of union - he was on the union meetings, he used to go to union meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That was the National Union of Miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 That's - yes. Federation of Miners union. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 
Not the Spencers' Union, he - he chucked it all up when the Spencers' Union was formed. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well you see - this coup belong
ed to the - that's Miners Federation Union and then they formed one - Mr Spencer - he sort of - well, they said he'd turned traitor. He was our Labour M.P. And he changed completely. And with that my husband - the - a lot of man had sack about Spencers Un
ion. Both at Mansfield district and all round here too. Lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 trouble}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 they had - and then you see they forced them to join this union but it wasn't called the Spencers Union in the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you belong to any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Sick funds or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh we used - we used to have savings stamps. Yes, we just had savings stamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about funerals, did you have a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No, we - we was insured against anything of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did either of you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were telling me you used to go out cycling a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, I did a lot of cycling when I - when I was in my teens - I did after I was married too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did either of you do any betting, gambling or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 My husband was dead against gambling. I used to have - a shilling on a - a big race any time but not as - as regards gambling. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Just like the Derby or the National or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. No, he was dead against gambling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go to any theatres, concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes, we used to go to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any hobbies, you did gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh - there was gardening was his most - took all his time up really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about you, did you have any other activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, only just going to whist drives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We had a dog. Yes. We always had a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You did gardening with your husband did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, I used to help him }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  a lot, you see, I used to do a lot of garden on the farm. Setting cow }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 cabbage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 plants with father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have any interests outside the home, other interests outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, I used to help people and anyone that was ill I used to help them. I did quite a lot of that. Sick nursing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you ever go out on your own to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, when we had a day from the - say the ladies outing from the chapel or anywhere like that. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Normally with the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did anyone outside the home help you to look after the house and the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well mother helped - if I ever wanted any help, but I always seemed to cope with it really. Unless I was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 If you were ill your mother normally came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, just came down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In what ways would she help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh well, she'd see to the children and she'd do the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 She would do this if you were confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes. I don't ever remember only having one long illness, that was - year before my son was born, June, 
1925, I had a illness and - bit of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11018113\charrsid10957874 bronchial}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 pneumonia but it passed off and I got better and I've never - I had to help mother from then really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You had your mother living by anyway didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes, she was close by, yes. I used to come every day to mother's. The latter part of her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes, here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I had quite a lot of friends used to come and see us. During - during the war we used to have little whist drives at home, to help.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 In your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you see your friends mainly at your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Sometimes in the week or weekends if it was too bad to go out, someone'd come - that had got no children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you and your husband share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes. Well he had - no, we had the same friends. Because the men that he worked with and his - the wives, I knew them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 Did either of you have any sort of separate friends that you had of your own?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No. No. No. 'Cos we always went together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You would invite friends into your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 How often approximately do you think people would come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well sometimes they'd come once a week or we'd go to their homes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was it normal in those days to offer them anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, I used to make them a cup of tea or if we - had - anything in, stout or anything - any - intoxicating, they'd have a drink. Those that cared to. Just now and again - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would you say that the friends invited in were your husband's or your own or shared friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - more my friends and they got to know him with knowing me you see. 'Cos they were the people that lived about here really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did any of them call in casually without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. A lot come, yes. And then see with having fowls they used to come for the eggs. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So it would be quite frequent then when they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And did neighbours call frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I never - never was one to go in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 neighbour\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  house unless I was wanted. My mother never did. No. Unless they was ill or wanted anything, it wasn't a matter of just nipping in the neighbour - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Would they call on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, because the - the people that lived up t
he street, there was some of them come - they was coming and going, there was eight houses up Baldwin Street in those days, there's more now. It's a little short street, yes, you can see like - this is where I lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Oh yes, I used to go and visit some of my friends. Some of them that - there are quite a few that - that used to go to the W.I. And then they sort of dropped it off during the war when we had to go in afternoon, but I've never left it of
f. I've gone to the W.I. right away from 1928.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 We're often told that in those days you made your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 own}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 There was no television or radio?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No nothing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 When you got together with your friends what sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
Well sometime we'd have a game of cards. Or dominoes, but we never played for money. No. Unless we was playing for - charities. And put so much down you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What about music, did you have musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh yes, we had quit
e a few musical evenings, because most of my friends have got pianos and - their children could play and we used to have a sing-song. Especially with going to the chapel when we had a concert coming off. Used to come to my place at Baldwin Street to rehea
rse. My husband's sat and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874  laughed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 many a half hour when we've been - dressed - go upstairs to dress up you know, then come down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Was your home rented, the one in Baldwin Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 It was a rented house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 He used to come once a fortnight. He lived up - Spring Gate, Kimberley. A very old gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think of him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Oh I thought nothing to him 'cos he was - whatever you tried to do but - I ma
de him do a lot of repairs because they was a necessity. And - he want - he had a - when rent started to go up and the rates he joined the Landlords Association. And I joined the Tenants. And this Mr Richmond, he was - he was as Labour man and he were a v
e
ry good man for advice. And - he didn't belong at anything, he was only an ordinary man. But anyway - I stuck to him, what he told me. What he told me what to do and what not to do. Well three of them in the yard where I lived in the fourth house, I was t
h
e top house - they - sort of afraid of the landlord. - But I told the landlord what I thought about him. And so one day he came and my husband was waiting, he said, I'll be in today when he comes. He used to come on a Saturday although it wasn't due 'til 
M
onday. But we allowed him that privilege. Anyway - he came in and he said - your wife's very stubborn. So my husband says, oh? I've not found that out. And he says, well, he says, you sit there and don't say a thing, he says, when my wife can't hold her o
w
n I'll take over. You see. And he said - yes, oh, he said, that's how it is. Well in my rent book, I could show it you if I could only - I don't know just where it is - he put me one and nine arrears. Oh I should think for nearly a quarter - two pages. I 
n
ever paid no rent. I wouldn't pay it. And he said, oh, he said, you'll go I don't know where. I said, well I shall be; ready to go Mr Sexton, I said, I don't mind. I said, I'm not paying you excess rates. I said, I know more about rates than what you so. 
I
've paid many a pound of rates to the Baseford Board of Guardians for my father and I know you're charging us too much. Well we only had an ordinary - toilet and there was two families to go to that. You see, there was no water closets in those days. We h
a
d to share it. And - I stuck out, I wanted a toilet on my own. Which I knew I could get, I'd had advice over it. Well then - this - a Mr Slater, he had an iron on his foot, he was a cripple, but he - he was a terror. And the talk he had to me was wicked, 
and he was going to send me to H.E. Donovan and I said, well look, if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 you\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  not careful I shall have you up for -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Send you to where did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 H.E.L.L. Only he said it straight out - to hell. Oh he said, before I - before I finish with you, h
e said, I'll send you to hell. I says, oh well, perhaps you'll be there first. I said, we're not talking like that Mr Slater. I said, you're not going to rob me. Well, these other - three tenants they give him their rent books, and he demanded mine. I sai
d, oh no. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 said,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 that my receipt for my rent. It was it. But I knew right, I knew I was doing right. Well - when their rent books come back he'd tore some out. The leaves out. And we had those rent books with a lot of writing on, not the plain ones, we had
 plain ones the year - when I first was married - and told you what you should do and what you shouldn't do. But when it come to my - my rent, - it was only four and six when I was married for the cottage. And it had been about six and tenpence ha'penny b
y
 the time this old Slater had finished with us. And so one day - I said, well Mr Slater, you've not been very kind to me, I says, and I don't want you to swear at me anymore, I said, I'm just going to tell you what kind of a man you are. And my husband sa
t
 there and heard me say it. And I never told him I was going to say it. He says, and what kind of man am I. I said, well when you're going along the street, I'm sorry that you're a cripple, but you're turning round every now and again, I says, is the old 
l
ad after you? He was furious. I don't know what he wasn't going to do to me. Anyway, I wouldn't have him in. He had to stay out - stay at the door. I said, I don't want to be rude to you but, I says, you get on with it and summons me - do just whatever yo
u
 like. But what do you think happened? I had all those weeks no rent to pay - I'd all these arrears crossed off and it's where he's put the pen through them. And this old gentleman - the landlord - he thanked - the - the others had paid, but they didn't g
et it back. And - this - he was robbing our landlord, this old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 andlord}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 \rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
 Association secretary and he was believing everything he said, what he could get for him you see. But I knew it wasn't right. And when it come to I lived rent free for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 another month}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 
. Well then the others - said, well why didn't I tell them. I says, I told you what I was doing, I wasn't paying. And of course when it come to I had won in the end, I knew I should win. And - my rent - my rent was down. Well then we had a toilet - the wa
t
er lavatory, the lot. Well one of the tenants said that I ought to pay more money than they did, they'd got a water lavatory. So I said, well I didn't see how that was fair. And of course that was all squashed. And we just had to pay the tuppence ha'penny
 extra rate - and I didn't even have to pay for the building of the toilet - we had to pay the tuppence ha'penny extra rate. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  how we went on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 You were living in the same community as you'd been living in as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12206649\charrsid10957874 child}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well - after the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 strikes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 worst}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 . Yes. We didn't have a struggle, we just go - went without }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 hings. We had food and paid }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  way. We never owed a penny. We could have had help from the council but we never went for any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What did you think about that time when you were having to go without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well I thought, it's come to something, but we'll have to make up for it when we can get going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 What difference did it make if your husband was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Well he was never ill. No. No, that's where the trouble came in. He was only out of work through }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  strike. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 So you never had to go to the Guardians for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 No, never. Never, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Your first child was a daughter named Mona?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Born on the 25th April, 1916? When she left school she went to work at the Wolsey factory at Kimberley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Which is a hosiery factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 And she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10383689\charrsid10957874 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874  a seamer on a machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12020912 RR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233194 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4936228\charrsid10957874 Until she was married?
